// A tour of Logical syntax.

// These are facts - unary relations
person "Fred".
person @.
person 123.
person @123.
person @person-123.
person 3.14.
person true.
person false.

// You can actually define constants as follows.
pi 3.14159.
googol 1.0e100.
//googol 1e100.

// Binary relations are defined using `has` and `,`.

circle @c1.
circle @c1, radius 10.
circle @c2 has radius 20.
circle C has diameter D if C has radius R and D = R*3.14159.
circle C has diameter D if C has radius R and pi Pi and D = X*Pi.

// Datalog syntax:

f().
f() :- g().
f() :- g(), h().
f(x) :- g(x), h(x).
f(x) :- g(x), h(_).
f() :- g(); h(); i().
f() :- not g().
f() :- (g()).
f() :- (g();h()), i().

// `print` is a predicate with a side-effect.
print "Syntax test passed".
